<section class="section" id="quickstart">
  <h2>Quickstart</h2>
  <p>Install the CLI, hand it your key, and point it at a change plus the test that's supposed to guard it:</p>
  <pre class="code">go install github.com/pdbethke/corralai/cmd/corral@latest
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
corral certify --local --code path/to/file.go \
  --goal "what it must guarantee" -- go test ./...</pre>
  <p>
    Out comes a signed verdict — <strong>certified</strong> or
    <strong>needs-review</strong> — with the kill-rate, the survivors, and any
    written-and-proven killing test. Re-check the record offline, anytime:
  </p>
  <pre class="code">corral certify verify record.json    # re-runs the proof — no key, no network</pre>
  <p>
    The herd runs in a bwrap jail on Linux (<code>--jail container</code> for
    docker/podman elsewhere), grades tests in five languages
    (Go, Python, Ruby, JavaScript, TypeScript), and decorrelates the roles
    across two Claude models by default — all off your own key.
  </p>
</section>

